# FR94 Content Ops — Cursor Rules

## Project Context

This project supports France94, an endurance and charity challenge where Jimmy will complete 94 Olympic-distance triathlons in 94 consecutive days, one per mainland French department, to raise money for cancer research.

This system is an internal AI-assisted content operations pipeline.

The goal is to turn raw media captured during training, planning, travel, outreach, and the challenge itself into structured content assets, approval-ready post candidates, and eventually final Instagram-ready drafts.

The human should stay involved only for approval and final judgment.

## Core Product Principle

This is not a generic social media scheduler.

It is a content intelligence system for a founder-athlete endurance project.

The pipeline should prioritize:

- raw authenticity

- mission clarity

- French-first communication

- international readability

- sponsor-safe output

- low manual admin

- deterministic infrastructure

- human approval before publishing

## Architecture Principle

Supabase is the source of truth.

Google Drive is raw file storage.

LLMs are used for semantic understanding, naming, captioning, and planning.

LLMs must not control orchestration, state transitions, deduplication, publishing, file permissions, or destructive actions.

Use normal deterministic code for:

- Drive scanning

- database reads/writes

- duplicate checks

- status changes

- file renaming

- error handling

- cron jobs

- permissions

- exports

Use AI only for:

- multimodal analysis

- transcript interpretation

- semantic summaries

- filename core suggestions

- content classification

- caption drafts

- post candidate generation

- production instructions
